Password That Can Be Set on Windows 7 Computer<br/><br/>The most common password used in windows 7 computer is the user account password, which can be set under User Account in Control Panel. Besides windows user password, there are other types of passwords on the computer. Let’s learn it one by one.
<br />If just when you start the computer, it asks for a password, this password may be power-on password, hard disk password or system password.
<br />How to set power-on password and hard disk password?
<br />1. Power on computer;
<br />2. Press F2 or other keys to login BIOS screen and select password tab;
<br />3. Choose Password and press Enter key with arrow keys;
<br />4. Input power on password or hard disk password, and press Enter key. Then confirm password as the wizard;
<br />5. Save all changes and logout BIOS screen by pressing F10 key;
<br />6. Restart computer.
<br />Tip: Different motherboards have various BIOS structure, just find to set password.
<br />How to set system password?
<br />1 To set system password, you need to set supervisor password as power-on password at first.
<br />2 Then go to security option under Advanced BIOS Features, change it from Setup to System.
<br />If you choose Setup, it will ask for password when you enter BIOS, which is BIOS password.  If you select System, it will require a password once you boot the computer, which is system password.
<br />All the above three kinds of passwords will be removed if supervisor password is cleared. But it is not an easy task to remove supervisor password if you forgot it, compared with the method to <a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5hbnlwYXNzd29yZHJlY292ZXJ5LmNvbS9yZXNldC13aW5kb3dzLTctcGFzc3dvcmQuaHRtbA__" target="_blank">reset windows 7 password</a> for user account. Therefore, keep supervisor password in mind.
